	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_25094309"><p>If he's a student, I hope Palin opts not to press charges, or pushes for a slap-on-the-wrist.  Some kind of punishment that will sting, but won't be career ending.</p><blockquote><div><p>Regardless of the politics involved, if there's no charges then any online email service is essentially useless for private communication.</p></div></blockquote><p>No, they are *already* useless for private communication.  Email is sent in plaintext across networks, and regardless of prosecution, the attack vector used here is a pretty easy one.  If your email is unencrypted, or you're using easily looked-up information as passwords or recovery questions, then it's not private.  period.</p><p>It would almost be better not to prosecute at all, if it has the effect of making people aware of, and take precautions against, the complete lack of privacy already extant.</p></div>
	</div>

